INSERT INTO questions (question, llama70b_response, llama1b_tailored_response, cosine_similarity) VALUES ('How do I stop being over possessive for a person whom I love?', 'To stop being overly possessive, recognize and acknowledge your feelings, then work on building trust and communication with your loved one. Set healthy boundaries and respect their independence, allowing them to make their own decisions and have their own space. By practicing self-reflection, open communication, and trust, you can cultivate a more balanced and secure relationship, reducing the urge to be overly possessive.', 'To stop being over possessive for a person you love, focus on building trust and open communication, allowing them to have their own space and autonomy. Recognize that their independence and individuality are essential to a healthy relationship, and avoid controlling or monitoring their actions. By letting go of the need to control and instead fostering a sense of mutual respect and trust, you can work to overcome possessive tendencies and develop a more balanced and secure relationship.', 0.8371240496635437);
