INSERT INTO questions (question, llama70b_response, llama1b_tailored_response, cosine_similarity) VALUES ('If CMYK printers create black by using colored ink and only complementing with black ink, why do shops charge more for color prints?', 'CMYK printers create black by combining cyan, magenta, and yellow inks, but this process can be imperfect and result in a dark brown color, which is why additional black ink is used to create a true black. When printing in color, all four inks (cyan, magenta, yellow, and black) are used, which increases the cost of ink and maintenance compared to printing in black and white, where only the black ink is used. As a result, shops charge more for color prints to account for the increased ink consumption and maintenance costs associated with using all four colors.', 'Many printers, including CMYK printers, use a combination of both colored ink and a small amount of black ink to create a darker, more complex black tone. The print quality and pricing of color prints are often higher because this combination of inks produces a deeper, richer black, as well as improved color accuracy and vibrancy compared to standard black ink alone.', 0.7749902009963989);
